Title: Don't fall for the hype!
Review:
I have read quite a number of books that ended up disappointing me. Some of those were gifted by well-meaning friends. Some of them were books I bought on an impulse. Then there were books that I had waited years to read only to find them unworthy of all those years of patience. But this book by Yuval Noah Harari tops the list. Just imagine reading a book that all your friends were going gaga about, only to find that there is nothing worthwhile in it and wondering whether you are really a good reader at all, now that you don’t even like a book that the whole world around you seems to love!

Let’s clear a few things first, before you think of bashing me up. This is a commendable effort by Mr. Harari to summarize the whole history of mankind and its evolutionary tale. During the initial pages, I too thought that this will be one of the best reads on anthropology. But this book promises a lot only to deceive. We statisticians use the term confirmation bias, which means the tendency to favor and present only those information that are supportive to one’s beliefs. This book is full of them. Harari had decided to present all that is wicked and weak about Homo Sapiens and he has succeeded to a large extent.

Not that I am complaining. I for one have never held the notion that we humans are special beings sitting atop the food chain, placed there by a favorable god who created us all in his (or, is it a ‘her’?) own image. I think of us as a different species of apes that managed to evolve a little quicker than our cousins. Despite our use of advanced languages, costly clothes and snazzy gadgets, internally we remain the beasts that roamed the vast forests once. I see nothing special about being human. This book helped cement that belief in my mind by discussing the idiocies and idiosyncrasies of our species as a whole.

But that’s just about it. This book isn’t ‘a brief history of humankind’, but the opinions of Mr. Harari about the various aspects of human evolution. This isn’t a chronological history in the lines of ‘What on Earth Happened?’ by Christopher Lloyd or ‘A Short History of Nearly Everything’ by Bill Bryson, both of which I found to be far more informative and interesting than this one. This is both a philosophical take and passing of judgments by Mr. Harari on what he considers to be the vital cogs of human evolution, namely Cognitive Revolution, Agricultural Revolution & Scientific Revolution. There is nothing that you end up learning that you already didn’t learn, especially in case you had read those two aforementioned books.

Sorry, dear friends. I have read much better books. 2.5 stars!

Title: A decent phone if you buy on deep discount days. Exynos processor dissapoints
Review:
It's a great phone to buy on Big sales or Deep discount sales days. The phone is definitely worth buying for 14k or less but not beyond that. The Exynos processor is what made me think twice. Would have beeen great if they had SD processor. Nontheless Exynos does a decent job but definitely nowhere near Qualcomm SD.

Pros
* Amoled - Display is pretty good
* Camera - Camera is extremely good for a phone priced at 14k
* Sound - Not that clear/sharp while attending calls but Ok, not bad either
* Battery - super good.. lasts 1 day on heavy use and 1.5days for normal use

cons
* Processor - Exynos instead of SD
* Battery charging - says fast charging but takes at least 2.5 hours for full charge
* Packaging - No laminated one time use screen protector (the laminated kind of sheet) is provided. Tempered glass has to be put immediately after receiving to prevent unnecessary scratches or damages.
* Silicon Cover - it would hardly cost 10/- or 20/- for the manufacturer, they should have provided a basic mobile cover
* Audio - not that great even with Samsung headphones..listening to music won't be a great experience even if you enable dolby or whatever the feature it has got
* Screen size - 6.7 inches would have been better
* Bloatware - Too many bloatware..unnecessary and annoying

Overall - It does a pretty good job. For 14k or below, just go for it..

after 3months of usage:
Phone is good, got android 11 update as well..
few annoying things to be noted are
1) during calls, the hold or record button gets enabled when the ear touches the sides of the pannels. I couldn't find a way to disable this on call menu. What I do is, put the phone into home screen and lock the screen as soon as I attend the call or when my calls gets picked

2) Bloatware - Too many bloatwares and Galaxy store updates apps of its liking. So I disbaled Galaxy store

3) Power cord - the length of the cord is way less than cords provided by any other brands. Apart from cutting cost by providing an inferior Exynos processor samsung wanna cut cost by cutting the cord's length.

4) Exynos is no where near SD

Title: Wonderful product for beginners!
Review:
Pros.
1. Super light weight as its made of aluminium and plastic
2. Has a spirit balance on top which helps to position the phone perfectly
3. The phone holder can be unscrewed and digital cameras can be fitted there
4. Rotation on all three axis are possible.
5. The legs can be extended 4fold to attain a height of about 4 feet
6. Rubber footing prevents slippage of legs.
Cons.
1. It is so lightweight that a tiny nudge makes it topple. Unsafe with children in house.
2. The plastic quality is a little questionable.
3. The phone holder has a spring that is extremely tight.

Conclusion.

Perfect for indoor videos and classes. Bang for the buck product. Did not expect soo fine a product at this cost. Spend some more if you have a studio or for outdoor photography

Title: Totally worth the money!!
Review:
I would say this as the best Value for Money keyboard+mouse combo. I purchased the product at 1159. Initially i didn't expect the product to be of top notch quality as its zebronics but this keyboard+mouse is of good build quality with brushed grey aluminium base and will suit for all entry level gamer's who want to look cool without spending much money.
Though the letters are not lit, the RGB lighting looks cool and has 3 modes with 3 levels of adjustable brightness. The mouse has a breather kind of RGB but there's no control to switch it off. The mouse has 4 dpi settings so that it'll suit for both gaming and casual use.

If you're restricted by budget, then you can go for it blindly!!

Title: Why to choose Crucial bx500 over samsung evo 860?
Review:
No issues while using it but I faced an issue while cloning it with my 1TB HDD (picture attached)..You may get this error while cloning larger HDD with a smaller SSD ..anyway I moved forward with this alert msg and got this done .
Why to choose Crucial BX500 Over samsung evo 860 (240GB) ?
1. Samsung evo 860 is expensive compared to the bx500.
2.During sale time samsung SSD could come to ₹3300, whereas I bought crucial SSD for ₹2500.
3.Performace wise you will not notice any difference both's speed are very much similiar. However samsung has some upper hand as far as some benchmarks considered.
4.The only con of BX 500 over evo 860 is bx500 has 3 years of warranty whereas evo 860 has 5 years of warranty.

Title: Very Good smart Watch in a Budget
Review:
I am very happy with my purchase. This is my 1st watch. I have used mostly all features in the 1 week I have used it.
1. It measures the BP, heart rate and SPO2 quite accurately
2. The steps counting is also fairly accurate
3. I set the feature on for walk reminder and it never fails to surprise me. Whenever I have been sitting for quite sometime, it vibrates and reminds me.
4. Women can track their monthly cycles too and set reminders
5. The dafit app is reasonably good but could be improved.

All in all a very good purchase to start with.

Title: Great printer
Review:
Model : L 3152
Seller : Appario Retail
Price : ₹10350
Bought on : 30th Sep, 2019
Extremely good product, print quality is excellent. Setup is also easy.
This product is very similar to L3150 but it has a blue highlight.
Before setting this up please read comprehensive user guide which is available in L3150 product page in pdf format. Trust me setup is very easy.
Many people are saying that WiFi setup is complicated but it's not. Using instruction anyone can setup wifi connection. From then it will connect automatically but it takes 1-2 minutes to connect. Till now I have not used the cable to connect the printer with computer, WiFi is all the thing.
N.B. : I have used WiFi direct option only.

Recap:
1. Fill the ink
2. Charge the ink
3. Run nozzle test (1 page)
4. Take a printout of WiFi password and all that stuff (3 pages)
5. Setup WiFi
5. Download Epson iPrint from Play store

Title: Must read book | Measure your growth
Review:
Before starting this book, write down some good habits you want to build and some bad habits you want to break. This book is filled with practical steps and examples. Yes, there are plenty of habit-building books out there (just as there are plenty of diet books but yet there are still more new books published every year). Plenty of people are seeking the right book that resonates with them. The key points in this book are:
* Compound Effect - Very small changes over time will have a big impact.
* Habit Building Techniques - Make good habits into routines; use positive reinforcements and other techniques outlined in the book.
* Monitor and Measure - Keep track of your progress and improvements.

Title: A phenomenal, revolutionary life changing book
Review:
As Jay Shetty mentioned in his book- Every time we do anything or dwell further into something that we like- we need to question ourselves ( our presence of mind and heart) : "What did I like about that?" Do I want to read about it, learn about it, spend my time doing it"
Am I here just for the outcome or I want to learn through the process of what it has in store to offer me?

As I further questioned myself with all these questions, I realized every word mentioned in the book was helping me become more self-aware of myself. It wasn't something that I was hearing for the first time but it was definitely something that my mind, body and soul was trying to tell me all this time but there was too much dust within my clogged thoughts and that's exactly what it helped me with- cleanse. This book has so magnificently captured and articulated emotions of a human mind, people's fear and how they overcome it and described it with examples that any person could relate to in his personal life. Every small details has been explained with verses from Bhagavad Gita and quotes said by famous personalities with examples. This book has not only asks you to read but it gives you activities to perform which help you in becoming more aware of your positives and negatives. Jay's words are so realistic and accomplishable that you'll feel driven to greet each day with discipline and motivation along with guidance that helps everyone achieve their destined journey. This book will successfully manage to break free from the perspective of the outside world and helps in conditioning the strong character in our own lives. I really want people to read this book as it helped me a lot in changing my mindset about my workplace and guided me to achieve my true dharma. Moreover, I truly believe this is just the beginning of the best services and dharma that the author is giving out to the world. And, I am definitely here for the learning process. The outcome will automatically come to us when we start growing exponentially as better individuals in our lives.

Title: Not like I hoped, but satisfied!!
Review:
I got the product in good condition, thanks to amazon and Acoustic World!

Product is good. It is comfortable for even long hours of usage, I am happy with that.

Earlier, I was using Sennheiser PX 80, I know it's not a fair comparison but that's what I was using :). So I heard a lot about audio-technica and watched so many review videos on youtube and decided to upgrade from my PX 80 to ATH-M50x. Considering the price of the device and the good reviews I watched on youtube, my expectations are sky high :) But in reality it is different, it is not that much of a big upgrade as I was hoping.

I don't know much technicality here but I am thinking if I have a separate DAC/amp then the sound quality would have been more pleasing. Like everybody knows the source audio should also be very good if you are expecting a good sound quality, in India most of the music streaming platforms gives 320 kbps(as per my knowledge), I won't say that is bad, but if you are hoping that with these headphones you are gonna blow your mind with superior sound quality then, well I don't know, maybe you should try with FLAC and good audio setup( I think like separate DAC/amp etc.)

So finally the conclusion is, if you are a person who listens to music from your phone or laptop then think about the money you are going to spend for this and if you are okay with that, go for it!!

Title: Okay mouse, very bad keyboard. Not worth the money.
Review:
A super cheap keyboard mouse combo.

Mouse:

Pros:

1. Main buttons are good. Tactile feel is okayish.

2. Pretty responsive mouse.

Cons:

1. Light as a feather. Needs to have some weight, some minimum weight.

2. Airy Side buttons though they work have no feel. People who experienced these kind of buttons can tell, they don't last more than a few days and also you can't physically feel any click, absolutely zero tactile feel except for a very faint click sound. So these are not really useful in gaming. You don't normally see these buttons anywhere, I saw these only once before on a very cheap Chinese made FM radio set as a on/off button.

3. Metal back plate will scratch your table.

Mouse Rating: 3/5 for this price.

Keyboard:

Pros:

Feel is somewhat mechanical.

Cons:

1. Very elevated: The metal plate lies flat on table and keys are very elevated. It's insanely difficult to type keeping your wrist straight. While gaming there is zero wrist support. Wrist starts to pain in a few minutes. Carpel tunnel is guaranteed. See pics attached.

2. The keyboard came very dusty and seems like used, see close up images attached.

3. The RGB is only RGB not key backlight. What do I mean, light comes from the gaps but not from the letters on the keyboard. Meaning you cannot see illuminated ABC etc, only light from all around the keys but actual keys don't glow. See pics attached.

4. There is no shread of ergonomics in the keyboard.

Keyboard Rating: 0/5

Okay mouse. Keyboard only good to hang as an RGB decoration.
